This paper deals with information flow analysis, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). It also discusses information theoretic metrics, which are related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper proposes solutions for conflict-free comparison of programs, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also deals with finite order deterministic programs, which is a topic in formal languages and automata theory (cs.LO). Finally, the paper proposes a technique for quantifying information leakage, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL).
